1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,931
Chapter 6 You Are What You Think You Are It's obvious.

2
00:00:07,120 --> 00:00:09,731
Much human behavior is puzzling.

3
00:00:10,080 --> 00:00:14,690
Have you ever wondered why a salesperson will greet one customer with an alert,

4
00:00:14,720 --> 00:00:18,771
yes sir, may I serve you, but virtually ignore another?

5
00:00:18,960 --> 00:00:23,091
Or why a man will open a door for one woman, but not for another?

6
00:00:23,361 --> 00:00:28,931
Or why an employee will consistently carry out the instructions of one superior,

7
00:00:28,960 --> 00:00:32,530
but only grudgingly do what another superior requests?

8
00:00:32,881 --> 00:00:38,290
Or why we will pay close attention to what one person says, but not to another?

9
00:00:38,721 --> 00:00:39,890
Look around you.

10
00:00:40,081 --> 00:00:45,091
You'll observe some people receiving the Hey Mac or Hey Buddy treatment,

11
00:00:45,121 --> 00:00:49,491
while others receive the sincere and important Yes Sir treatment.

12
00:00:49,841 --> 00:00:50,610
Watch.

13
00:00:50,721 --> 00:00:57,411
You'll observe that some people command confidence, loyalty, and admiration, while others do not.

14
00:00:58,081 --> 00:01:06,370
Look closer still, and you'll also observe that those persons who command the most respect are also the most successful.

15
00:01:06,801 --> 00:01:08,370
What is the explanation?

16
00:01:08,481 --> 00:01:12,051
It can be distilled into one word, thinking.

17
00:01:12,241 --> 00:01:14,451
Thinking does make it so.

18
00:01:14,881 --> 00:01:17,891
Others see in us what we see in ourselves.

19
00:01:18,241 --> 00:01:22,051
We receive the kind of treatment we think we deserve.

20
00:01:22,721 --> 00:01:24,930
Thinking does make it so.

21
00:01:25,201 --> 00:01:32,131
The fellow who thinks he is inferior, regardless of what his real qualifications may be, is inferior.

22
00:01:32,481 --> 00:01:34,930
for thinking regulates actions.

23
00:01:35,121 --> 00:01:43,891
If a man feels inferior, he acts that way, and no veneer of cover-up or bluff will hide this basic feeling for long.

24
00:01:44,161 --> 00:01:47,730
The person who feels he isn't important isn't.

25
00:01:48,161 --> 00:01:53,650
On the other side, a fellow who really thinks he is equal to the task is.

26
00:01:54,481 --> 00:01:59,091
To be important, we must think we are important, really think so.

27
00:01:59,201 --> 00:02:01,411
Then others will think so too.

28
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:03,570
Here again is the logic.

29
00:02:03,841 --> 00:02:06,931
How you think determines how you act.

30
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:12,131
How you act, in turn, determines how others react to you.

31
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:19,811
Like other phases of your personal program for success, winning respect is fundamentally simple.

32
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:24,851
To gain the respect of others, you must first think you deserve respect.

33
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:30,051
And the more respect you have for yourself, the more respect others will have for you.

34
00:02:30,480 --> 00:02:32,051
Test this principle.

35
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:35,491
Do you have much respect for the fellow on Skid Row?

36
00:02:35,601 --> 00:02:36,531
Of course not.

37
00:02:36,640 --> 00:02:37,251
Why?

38
00:02:37,441 --> 00:02:40,371
Because the poor fellow doesn't respect himself.

39
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:44,450
He's letting himself rot away from lack of self-respect.

40
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:48,450
Self-respect shows through in everything we do.

41
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:57,811
Let's focus our attention now on some of the specific ways we can increase self-respect and thereby earn more respect from others.